              "cf": "",
              "x": "The spleen is an organ located in the upper left side of the abdomen, beneath the ribcage, and is part of the lymphatic system."
            },
            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "The spleen plays a crucial role in filtering blood, removing old or damaged red blood cells, and helping to fight infections."
            },
            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "In some animals, such as dogs, the spleen can contract and release stored blood in times of need, such as during exercise or in response to injury."
            },
            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "Enlargement of the spleen, known as splenomegaly, can occur due to various conditions, including infections, liver disease, or blood disorders."
            },
            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "The spleen also serves as a reservoir for platelets and white blood cells, releasing them into circulation as needed to support the immune response."
            }
          ]
        }
